RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 12500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibi lity).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHROME HEIR settled off the rail, challenged approaching the three eighths pole and dueled for the nod past the five sixteenths, drew clear toward the quarter and held on well under steady handling. STRONG HEART rated close toward the inside, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn but had to settle for second best. TYRY TYRANNOSAURUS rated close off the rail, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and dueled through the stretch for third. CAIRO BOOGIE saved ground off the pace, eased out into the backstretch and bid past the seven sixteenths pole, left the far turn about the four path and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. WICKOSITY saved ground well off the pace, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, angled to the five path leaving the turn and flattened in the lane. GANDHI'S ORION took the lead at the mile pole and rated a short lead inside, came under pressure nearing the three eighths, was met and dueled past the pole, gave up the lead at the five sixteenths, dropped back approaching the quarter and weakened in the stretch. ADARA settled in the four path early on, raced two deep on the second turn and showed little response through the backstretch. LUCKY MUCHO MAN settled in the three and four paths, gave chase toward the three eighths pole but weakened approaching the far turn. EISELE raced well off the pace and showed little response. SIMILAR TASTE rated close to the early pace but weakened after a half mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Strong Heart
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,bid 3/8,2d far turn,settled 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 15200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE NOVEMBER 5, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since November 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5 ,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRANDIOSELY was bumped out leaving the gate then closed to the lead nearing the seven sixteenths pole and rated the pace, dueled clear toward the quarter and dug in under steady handling to hold on. BLACK PANDA engaged in close chase inside, dropped back approaching the quarter pole, raced near the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. FORTES was bumped then pinched back at the start, picked up the chase past the chute, raced off the rail on the turn, angled out leaving the turn and finished well while gaining on the runner-up. SMOOTH AS GLASS chased through the backstretch, raced near the rail on the turn and finished evenly to pass rivals. MS HEADLEY came out and made contact with Grandiosely leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, but was forced out leaving the turn and flattened in the lane. SECRET AFFIRMATION chased, raced in the three path of the turn and flattened the final sixteenth. THUNDER PUNCH broke in and made contact with Fortes, gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path and weakened. SOME IS NINE chased, rounded the turn in the five path and showed little in the lane. MIDNIGHT FLING gave chase outside, rounded the turn about the six path and weakened. Hot Carol became very fractious in the gate and was a late scratch.

ENTRY.NAME: Grandiosely
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,up 7/16,rated pace,dueled clear,held on driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 5 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since March 5 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $15,0 00 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNISON became a bit anxious in the gate, came away awkwardly and exchanged contact with Hopping Henry at the break then dueled at even terms from the seven sixteenths pole, drew clear two deep toward the eighth pole and was kept alert through the lane. FIZBO was hustled to even terms and contested the pace from the seven sixteenths pole, raced close at the rail on the turn but dropped back toward the eighth pole and ran evenly in the stretch. HOPPING HENRY exchanged contact with Unison leaving the gate, gave chase outside, raced in the four path on the turn and cleared third inside the sixteenth pole. SETTLEMENT DATE chased, raced off the rail on the turn then flattened the final sixteenth. DRINKWITHTHESTARS chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn then flattened later yards. SARGENT KOBE was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Fizbo
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled up,dueled even terms,close rail turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Drinkwiththestars
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8, 000 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEST VIRGINIA became a bit edgy in the gate then rated close off the rail, gave chase into the backstretch, dueled at even terms from the three eighths pole, contested the far turn two deep and dug in determinedly to inch clear of HANDSOME JOANIE later yards. The latter drew clear leaving the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and dueled gamely to mid-stretch before relenting. HERETODAYGONMANANA came away awkwardly then steadied, rated close to the early pace inside, closed to the heels of Handsome Joanie nearing the three eighths pole, angled out and gave chase past the pole, rounded the far turn near the rail then flattened the final sixteenth. MY SISTER PAM rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and flattened in the lane. TENNIS TAP rounded the opening turn about the three path, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and showed little in the lane. WEST VIRGINIA PAM settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path then flattened. WOODSONG'S CASTLE showed little response. DIXIE YODELER raced off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened off the rail on the far turn. HOW IS SHE rounded the first turn about the five path, left the turn outside and showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Best Virginia
ENTRY.OWNER: O'Sullivan Farms LLC and Conrad Randall R

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 90. Starter Allowance Purse 21700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE MAY 5, 2021. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since March 5 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WELLING raced with the early pace inside, was met at the nine sixteenths pole and settled close, recovered the lead past the seven sixteenths, drew clear approaching the three eighths and came under pressure leaving the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and was steadily handled in the lane. JAYJAYDEE rounded the first turn about the five path then saved some ground on the second turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced close off the rail on the far turn and settled for second best. RAISE A SPEIGHTS rounded the first turn about the four path, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. LOKOYA ROAD settled off the rail, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, eased out leaving the turn but showed little in the lane. CANTAKEITANYMORE rounded the first turn about the three path, picked up the chase into the backstretch, rounded the far turn about the four path, was forced out leaving the turn and could only improve position. UNEQUIVOCAL rounded the first turn in the four path, moved to the inside on the second turn and gave chase leaving the half mile pole, raced in the three path of the far turn, angled out into the lane but showed little more. GOLDEN APPEAL raced with the pace two deep, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and weakened in the lane. JAMMIN STILL rounded the opening turn about the six path, raced well back from the second turn and was not a factor. BIG DADDY D R rounded the first turn in the four path, closed to the lead nearing the three quarter pole but raced wide into the second turn, drew to even terms at the nine sixteenths pole, was met at the seven sixteenths and showed little more.

ENTRY.NAME: Lokoya Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,chased near 3/8,rail far turn,eased out 1/8,empty lane

ENTRY.NAME: Raise a Speights
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p 1st turn,off pace,chased 7/16,off rail far turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HE IS BONAFIDE pressured the early pace inside, was steadied at the rail off the heels of Wayne's Hope past the three eighths pole but recovered stride quickly, took the lead two deep approaching the top of the lane, raced clear past the eighth pole and was steadily handled to widen. DANCIN IN DUBAI was bumped leaving the gate then gave chase outside, rounded the turn about the six path, left the turn wide but finished well to take second the final strides. D TACHYON exchanged contact with Just Go With It leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, raced in the three path on the turn, dug in leaving the turn but was nipped from second in the final strides. WAYNE'S HOPE drew clear while tapering toward the inside and set a pressured pace, rounded the turn near the rail, was met approaching the eighth pole, dropped back leaving the pole and weakened the final sixteenth. STRONG MAGIC chased inside, rounded the turn at the rail and flattened in the lane. BARB'S PRIDE chased, raced off the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. KING T'CHALLA ducked in at the break and made contact with Dancin In Dubai then bobbled, gave chase through the backstretch, raced in the six path on the turn and weakened in the lane. JUST GO WITH IT exchanged contact with D Tachyon leaving the gate and saved ground. TANELEER engaged in close chase through the backstretch, raced off the aril on the turn and weakened in the stretch. TEMPTING MOMENT became edgy in the gate and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Barb's Pride
ENTRY.OWNER: P and H Stables and C and B Stables

ENTRY.NAME: Dancin in Dubai
ENTRY.OWNER: Irish Hill Century Farm and McGuire Matthew

ENTRY.OWNER: Gilbert Melissa Rentz and Oxendine Martin

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 91. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 32700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 5 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since March 5 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BABY MAN rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, took the lead two deep midway on the far turn and was steadily handled in the stretch. MY FLICKER rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase from the half mile pole and raced close in the three path on the far turn, dug in from the head of the lane and just lasted for second. AZZURRA raced well off the pace in the three path on the first turn, gave chase into the backstretch, rounded the far turn about the five path, dug in through the stretch and just missed second. ALPINE MOON saved ground off the pace on the first turn, gave chase leaving the half mile pole, raced boxed at the heels of Complete Surprise at the rail on the far turn and ran evenly through the lane. LACE REVOLUTION saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, angled out leaving the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. COMPLETE SURPRISE rated the pace inside, came under pressure nearing the seven sixteenths pole, was met at the rail approaching the eighth pole and weakened in the stretch. HASHTAG LUCKY took a brief early lead then stalked off the rail on the first turn, challenged at the seven sixteenths pole, raced close through the far turn but faded approaching the head of the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Azzurra
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace 3p,chased 1/2,5p far turn,just missed 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 1/2,boxed rail far turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.OWNER: Fanelli John and Longball Stables LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPARKLING SHIRE saved ground off the pace, closed the gap from the seven sixteenths pole, took the lead at the rail nearing the quarter and was steadily handled to widen through the lane. OBOY rated close off the rail, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, cleared second past the eighth pole but was no match in the lane. SPEIGHTY SENSE took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, dug in to the challenge of Voice Of Now leaving the nine sixteenths pole, cleared that one toward the three eighths but was caught approaching the quarter and weakened. MY SLICK NICK settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the nine sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the six path and finished evenly to improve his position. FLASH OF DAY became unsettled and hopped at the break, stalked from the three path on the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and flattened stride. BIG REDWHITEBLUE raced well off the pace in the three path on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the seven path and showed little in the lane. VOICE OF NOW rounded the first turn about the four path then challenged two deep from the nine sixteenths pole but dropped back at the three eighths and faded in the four path on the far turn. ARMOR PIERCING showed little response. BAL ROBINSON raced in the five path the first turn, gave chase past the half mile pole but faded through the backstretch. REAL RAMBO saved ground.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close off rail,chased 7/16,rail far turn,no match
